ng consumption and demand, developing sustainable food and energy sources, and addressing poverty. Their multidisciplinary perspective encompasses such approaches as school gardens, using school buildings as teaching tools, and the greening of schoolyards. Arguing for a paradigm shift in the way we view education as a whole, The Failure of Environmental Education demonstrates how our education system can create new levels of awareness and work toward a sustainable future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEnvironmental education. 70(DE-601)1061350150(DE-588)4061627-7aUmwelterziehung2gnd 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aalternative energy.  aamerican education.  abiodiversity.  aclimate change.  aconservation.  aconsumption.  aearth.  aeducation policy.  aeducation.  aendangered animals.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental education.  aenvironmental history.  aenvironmental psychology.  aenvironmental writing.  aenvironmentalism.  aextinction.  aglobal warming.  agreen habits.  agreen living.  agreen schools.  anature.  ano child left behind.  anonfiction.  apedagogy.  apolitics.  apoverty.  apublic schools.  arecycling.  aschool gardens.  ascience.  asocial issues.  asustainability.  asustainable lifestyle.1 aBlumstein, Daniel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026538740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094872340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948723423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948723/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGB